{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"Only files changed in the pull request are analyzed — unchanged files are not scanned.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"MOCK-MISS/MOCK-HIDE: a mocked changed-file list can hide real failures in PR file discovery (renames, pagination, path filtering). REAL-INFRA: this boundary depends on real PR/diff acquisition in CI (GitHub Action context + git/GitHub data), so the minimum realistic failure-catching test is system-level.","test_description":"Run the action in a CI-like environment against a real test PR containing a known mix of changed and unchanged files; assert that only PR-changed paths are passed to linting and that no findings reference unchanged files.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.08,"Integration":0.32,"System":0.6,"Agentic":0.0,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"Findings are grouped by severity (error, warning, info) in the posted PR comment.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"MOCK-MISS: pure unit tests on formatter logic can miss wiring bugs between parser/aggregator/comment builder. REAL-INFRA is not required to validate grouping correctness; posting can be captured via local adapter. So integration is the minimum boundary that catches real grouping failures.","test_description":"Feed representative linter outputs through the real parsing + aggregation + comment-render pipeline (with a local fake comment sink) and assert the emitted comment has correctly separated error/warning/info sections with the right findings in each.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.22,"Integration":0.7,"System":0.08,"Agentic":0.0,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"A pull request that touches 200 files completes analysis within the 10-minute Actions timeout.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"REAL-INFRA: timeout behavior depends on real runtime constraints (CPU, I/O, subprocess overhead, CI environment). MOCK-HIDE: mocked timing or mocked linter execution can falsely pass. Therefore minimum is system-level performance testing under CI-like conditions.","test_description":"Execute the full action on a generated PR-sized corpus (200 changed files) in GitHub Actions (or a faithfully equivalent runner), measure end-to-end wall-clock time, and fail if completion exceeds 10 minutes.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.0,"Integration":0.04,"System":0.96,"Agentic":0.0,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"When the linter process crashes on a malformed file, the remaining files are still analyzed and results posted.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"REAL-INFRA: crash handling is at subprocess/process-boundary level. MOCK-HIDE: if linter is mocked, true crash/exit-signal behavior is hidden. The minimum test must exercise a real crashing linter process and verify continuation + final comment posting path.","test_description":"Run the pipeline with a real linter subprocess where one crafted file triggers a hard crash/non-zero fatal exit; assert the runner isolates that failure, continues analyzing other files, and posts a PR comment containing surviving results plus crash notice.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.16,"System":0.82,"Agentic":0.0,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"Duplicate findings on the same line from overlapping rules are deduplicated in the output.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"MOCK-MISS: a unit test on a dedup helper may miss real duplicate-shape differences introduced by parser/rule normalization. REAL-INFRA is unnecessary; no OS/network dependency is required. Minimum is integration across finding ingestion, normalization, and output rendering.","test_description":"Use real linter outputs (or fixtures in real output format) containing overlapping-rule duplicates on identical file/line/severity, pass through the full aggregation pipeline, and assert one emitted finding per dedup key in the posted-output payload.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.34,"Integration":0.62,"System":0.04,"Agentic":0.0,"Workflow":0.0}}]}
